name: What is palm Sunday
summary: Palm Sunday, commemorating Jesus' triumphant entry into Jerusalem, marks the beginning of Holy Week, a significant period in Christianity. It is celebrated with Palm Processions, a tradition derived from biblical accounts, symbolizing Jesus' reception as the Messiah. The Gospel of Matthew and Mark both describe this event, but with slight variations, leading to the question of why there are two versions of the narrative. Furthermore, the significance and global celebrations of Palm Sunday are explored, along with reflections on its spiritual meaning. Despite Pope Francis' unusual decision to skip the homily during the Palm Sunday Mass, he addressed the crowd during the Angelus later in the day. Finally, information regarding the date of Easter 2024 is provided, as Palm Sunday precedes Easter by one week, marking the start of the most important week in Christian history.

name: Palm Sunday
summary: Palm Sunday marks the beginning of Holy Week, a period of great significance in Christianity. As per the accounts in two Gospels (Matthew and John), on Palm Sunday, Jesus Christ triumphantly entered Jerusalem, greeted by people waving palm branches. Catholics hold a Palm Procession on this day to commemorate this event and acknowledge Jesus as king. Pope Francis, however, skipped the customary Palm Sunday homily, making it an unusual decision for a major event. Palm Sunday is a time for reflection and preparation for the somber events to follow during the week. It is observed with special customs and festivities around the world, such as waving palm branches and attending special church services.

name: Peter Angelos
summary: Peter Angelos, the former owner of the Baltimore Orioles, has passed away at the age of 94. Angelos was a prominent figure in professional baseball, owning the Orioles for over two decades. He was also known for his involvement in the 1994-95 MLB labor stoppage, where he played a key role in resolving the dispute. Beyond his contributions to baseball, Angelos was a successful lawyer and philanthropist who dedicated himself to fighting for the rights of the underprivileged.
